All sane, intelligent adults are responsible for their own actions. It's a fact not an opinion. Many of those otherwise sane, intelligent adults have convinced themselves that someone else is to blame for their lot in life but they are lying to themselves. I'll happily use myself as an example...<br>
<br>
Homeless: Check<br>
Grow up with junkies: Check<br>
Parental neglect: Check<br>
Total failure of the State to intervene: Check<br>
etc: Check<br>
<br>
I started out with NOTHING and worked my way to a damn good job, a stable, happy marriage, a wonderful son, and a pretty damn good life. I did it on my own because through all the crap I dealt with growing up I understood that the only way I could fail was to pawn my issues off on someone else. Whining, bitching folks blaming their bad decisions on their government, their friends, or their family make me sick. Your father beat you? Too damn bad, be an adult and move on. Make up for it by being a good parent to your own kids. You grew up poor, ant the other kids made fun of your clothes? Too damn bad, be an adult and move on. Kids make fun of other kids. If your clothes were in style they would have made fun of your hair or your name.<br>
<br>
The world owes you nothing. Take responsibility for yourself.<br>
