<br>
'Trust me, you can't outdo me on personal tragedy...if I can move on so can anyone'<br>
- I don't trust you. Because what you've accomplished isn't default for everyone else. People ALWAYS have the ability, I'm not saying we don't. I am saying that people aren't as great as you, as 'superiorly strong' as you. People suffer, and as unbelievable as it seems, more than you. And some don't make it, they don't find the will power to over come the past. But you know what.. that's ok too. People in life aren't always going to live up to your expectations. Ever seen Magnolia? A great movie, and the pinacle for what I mean. Some may beat the past, but for others, they may be through with it, but it isn't through with them.<br>
Ever heard of a guy called Talcot Parsons? Big on functionalism and a theory called Symbolic interactionism. I'm no small scale interationist, but I do see his point when he states that we are defined by others, our life, our mentality. We are shaped, and therefore we act the way we have grown. <br>
<br>
'Get out of jail free cards for everyone! Tell them Halo sent you'<br>
- Now perk up your ears. I'm not saying that tommorrow you can go on a masacre in the middle of a 'mall' and it's fine because you were beaten with a stick early on in life. I'm not saying you can go around sexually abusing people because you yourself were sexually abused. <br>
I'm saying that these people need help. They need us. There is always a reason. There is no good, no bad, just what exists. People do things, everyone does things. No one follows the 10 fucking commandments like a prick. Some sway more than others, and my point is we aren't monsters, we aren't barbarians. No. As much as you'd like to scapegoat these people with a label that just frankly doesn't exist - well you can't. Bursting your bubble. These people are us. They are not evil, they are not the devil. <br>
Oh frig, I've rambled on enough. 11hr shifts kill ya.<br>
Now to finish off christmas turkey. I'll be having it for breakfast, lunch, and dinner for the next 2 weeks I think. <br>
God help me.<br>
<br>
<br>
